headline: McDonald’s vs. Yum! Brands: Which Wins the Battle for India as US Growth Slows?
summary: McDonald’s (NYSE: MCD) and Yum! Brands (NYSE: YUM) face a punishing domestic landscape. headline: McDonald's (NYSE:MCD) Exceeds Q4 CY2025 Expectations
summary: Fast-food chain McDonald’s (NYSE:MCD) reported revenue ahead of Wall Street’s expectations in Q4 CY2025, with sales up 9.7% year on year to $7.01 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $3.12 per share was 2.2% above analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: McDonald’s Says Its Value Campaign Is Paying Off
summary: McDonald’s  said that its multiyear quest to make its food more affordable is working.  The world’s largest burger chain reported a 5.7% growth in same-store sales across its regions in the three months ended Dec. 31, outpacing analysts’ expectations for the quarter.  The chain’s total revenue also beat expectations.

headline: McDonald's says focus on value is bringing back customers
summary: McDonald's focus on value is paying off. The fast food giant said Wednesday that its global same-store sales — or sales at locations open at least a year — jumped 5.7% in the October-December period. That's better than the 3.9% Wall Street was expecting, according to analysts polled by FactSet.
